cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.LO, cs.DB, cs.CL 

This paper discusses the use of Description Logics (DLs) in the context of Multimedia Information Retrieval (MIR), which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper proposes a fuzzy extension of DLs, which could fall under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of DLs for managing structured knowledge, which could be related to cs.DB (Databases).
